This is the best alarm clock I have used, and I've tried about 5 of them. It is simple to set a basic alarm. But there are many,  many features that allow you to almost endlessly customize the whole app if you choose. For example, if I wanted to change all the sounds for a bunch of alarms at once, I can do it easily -- no need to go into each alarm's settings. It also allows you to setup many different categories to group your alarms into, to keep the main screen from getting cluttered with alarms. It is very useful to me to be able to separate the alarms I want to go off on a permanent basis, from those that are one-time reminders to do something today (or at any future date). There are very flexible settings for the snooze function: you can set a default and all future alarms will use that snooze interval. Or you can set it to ask you what you want the snooze duration to be each time the snooze runs out. I've moved most of the calendar reminders from Outlook to Smart Alarm.  Being able to so flexibly remind myself of important tasks throughout the day cuts my anxiety level way down because I no longer have to worry about not remembering something important to do.
